B26 - Help another student in this unit struggling to understand/learn a cybersecurity concept

Objective
The goal of this activity was to help another student understand basic cybersecurity concepts and improve their awareness of common online security threats.

Method
I explained key cybersecurity concepts to another student through an instagram chat conversation. The focus was on making topics simple and relevant to everyday online activities, such as social media use and account security.

Content covered
1. Multi-Factor Authentication - I explained that MFA adds an extra layer of security by requiring a second verification step in addition to a passrod.
2. Phishing attacks - I explained how phishing works by using fake messages or links that attempt to trick users into revealing sensitive information such as passwords pr login details

Outcome
The student gained a clearer understanding of both MFA and phishing attempts work and understood why enbaling MFA improves account security.

Reflection
This activity helped reinforce my own understanding of cybersecurity concepts by requiring me to explain them in a simpe and practical way. It also highlighted how common security risks like phishing rely heavily on user awareness, and how small actions such as enabling MFA can siginificantly improve account safety.
